title: Woman killed as speeding SUV rams scooty, drags it in city
description: In a tragic hit-and-run in Paschim Vihar, Delhi, a woman lost her life after an SUV collided with their scooty. Her son got injured in the incident. The driver is still at large.

title: Bloody Monday: Six murders reported in capital on Holi
description: Six Holi murders reported involving Alipur, Gulabi Bagh, northeast Delhi, Mangolpuri, Shahdara, and outer Delhi. Victims include a woman, Mustakim, Kamil, and Rajkaran. Arrests made in most cases.

title: Baba Kalyani's niece, nephew move court over family assets
description: Sameer Hiremath and Pallavi Swadi - grandchildren of forging industry pioneer Neelkanth Kalyani - have moved Pune civil court against their uncle and Bharat Forge chairman Baba Kalyani, seeking division of family assets. They have demanded one-ninth of the family estate including stakes in Bharat Forge and Kalyani Steel as their share.

title: Bridge collapses after snag-hit freighter rams it in US; 6 missing
description: A freight ship collision at Baltimore port with a bridge has caused chaos and closures. The Indian crew reported a 'power issue,' while rescuers search the Patapsco river. The incident may disrupt car and coal supplies.

title: 3 Rajiv Gandhi killers will be deported to Sri Lanka in a week
description: Tamil Nadu government informed Madras high court on Tuesday that Sri Lankan deputy high commission has issued temporary travel documents to three convicts in the Rajiv Gandhi assassination case - Sriharan alias Murugan, Robert Payas & Jayakumar. They will be deported to Sri Lanka within a week or once the deportation orders are issued by Foreigners Regional Registration Office (FRRO), additional public prosecutor R Muniyapparaj informed a division bench of Justices R Sureshkumar and K Kumaresh Babu.

title: Curb media reports only in exceptional cases: Supreme Court
description: The Supreme Court stresses protecting journalistic freedom amidst legal action by powerful entities. It warns against hasty restraining orders, emphasizing the need for evidence of 'malicious' content. Justices caution on the impact of pre-trial injunctions on free speech and public debate. The ruling reaffirms the balance between free speech and reputation in media defamation cases.

title: DGCA's revised rules on pilots' duty, rest time put on hold
description: Indian aviation regulator has suspended the implementation of new rules on airline pilots' duty and rest time. Airlines can follow the old regulations until new guidelines are approved, after a pilot's tragic death raised concerns about fatigue. The Directorate General of Civil Aviation introduced revised Flight Duty Time Limitations (FDTL) norms to address pilot fatigue.

title: Ex-CM Beant's grandson Bittu, Congress MP from Ludhiana, in BJP
description: Ravneet Singh Bittu, transitioning from Congress to BJP in Punjab, aims to influence state politics by contesting from Ludhiana. His move follows BJP's choice to independently participate in the elections, impacting Punjab's political landscape.

title: With Congress, AAP also going solo, Punjab to see 4-cornered fight
description: Announcing that the party would contest Lok Sabha elections in Punjab on its own, state BJP president Sunil Jakhar said the decision was made after gathering feedback from party leaders and cadre. BJP has conveyed its unwillingness to accede to any conditions set forth by Shiromani Akali Dal (SAD), with which the party was seeking to renew its alliance, reported.

title: PM Modi, Belgian PM discuss Gaza, Ukraine
description: PM Modi and Belgian PM De Croo discussed Ukraine war, West Asia conflict, India-Belgium relations, Nuclear Energy Summit, trade, investment, clean technologies, semiconductors, pharmaceuticals, green hydrogen, IT, defence, and ports.

title: After polls, J&K police alone will handle law & order: Amit Shah
description: Union home minister Amit Shah shared a seven-year plan to transfer law and order duties from central troops to Jammu and Kashmir police, emphasising the increased role of the state police in anti-terror operations. The discussion also included the nullification of Article 370, BJP's electoral prospects, and actions against terrorist organisations.

title: Cong pledges national minimum wage at Rs 400 a day if voted to office
description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge said the real wage increase in 10 years of Modi govt has been less than 1%, while it was 8.6% for agriculture and 6.9% for non-agriculture sectors, respectively, during 2009-14 under UPA govt. The announcement appears to be aimed at national floor level minimum wage which is Rs 176 at present.

title: In a 1st, Mumbai pips Beijing, is Asia's billionaire capital
description: Mumbai overtakes Beijing to become Asia's leading billionaire hub with 92 billionaires and $445 billion wealth, driven by energy and pharmaceutical sectors. New York tops globally with 119 billionaires, followed by London. Indian billionaires like Mukesh Ambani and Gautam Adani make significant strides in wealth. Mumbai's rise attributed to 26 new billionaires and 47% wealth growth.

title: In 6th suicide in Kota this year, NEET aspirant kills himself
description: Mohammad Urooj, 20, died by suicide in Kota PG, sixth student suicide this year. No note, autopsy pending. Unanswered calls alerted parents. Lack of anti-suicide device noted, under investigation.

title: BJP leader Dilip Ghosh questions Didi's 'parentage', EC seeks report
description: "Didi goes to Goa and says she is Goa's daughter, goes to Tripura and says she is Tripura's daughter...," Ghosh said during a media interaction in Durgapur before going to make the deprecatory remarks. EC later sought a report from Burdwan (West) district administration. "Such comments... constitute an attack on her (Mamata's) personal character and modesty, and amount to a blatant violation of code of conduct," Trinamool wrote to EC.

title: Don't obey govt order to deposit arms: Manipur tribal outfit
description: ITLF urged Kuki-Zo against firearm deposit, stressed defense. LS seats polls on April 19, Outer Manipur vote on April 26 for life, land protection.

title: Abstinence from political activity can't be bail condition: SC
description: Supreme Court rejects bail condition of 'non-participation in political activities', quashing Orissa HC's order. Petitioner's attempt to withdraw the condition was denied, leading to SC intervention citing fundamental rights violation.

title: Punjab Cong averse to joining INDIA bloc rally in Kejriwal's support
description: There is no official communication yet from the high command about participating in the March 31 rally, but most Punjab Congress leaders are averse to the idea and have instead called for going all-out against Bhagwant Mann-led AAP govt. Despite no tie-up in Punjab, both parties remain part of INDIA bloc at national level, with seat-sharing agreements in Delhi, Haryana, Gujarat, Goa and Chandigarh.

title: Karnataka man loses Rs 1.5cr in IPL betting, wife kills self
description: A Karnataka family faces tragedy as online cricket betting leads to crores in debts, suicide, and arrests due to creditors' harassment, reflecting the dire consequences of the husband's actions.

title: After row, Congress netas say post on Kangana not their handiwork
description: Shrinate and Ahir claimed the post was not put out by them and they are trying to find out who posted it. Congress said it has always believed that there is no space for such language in public discourse and the matter should end with Shrinate clearing the air. NCW chairperson Rekha Sharma, in a letter to CEC Rajiv Kumar, referred to the remarks as "derogatory and outrageous to dignity of a woman".

title: BJP tickets for 6 Himachal Congress rebels spark dissent
description: Shortly after BJP's announcement, former minister and party leader from Lahaul and Spiti assembly constituency Ram Lal Markanda resigned and indicated that he might contest as a Congress candidate. Markanda's decision was prompted by the nomination of Congress rebel Ravi Thakur, who had defeated him in the previous assembly elections. All office-bearers of the BJP's Lahaul and Spiti block unit resigned in protest against the party's decision.

title: PM Modi talks to Sandeshkhali survivor, hails her courage
description: ​Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Tuesday praised Rekha Patra - one of the several survivors of the alleged largescale sexual violence and land grab at Sandeshkhali in West Bengal and who has been nominated by BJP for the Basirhat Lok Sabha seat - and called her "Shakti Swaroopa" for showing the courage to register the first FIR against the Trinamool strongman allegedly responsible for her ordeal.

title: Atal pension plan 'coercive', says Jairam, finance minister returns fire
description: A debate between finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman and Congress member of parliament Jairam Ramesh on the Atal Pension Yojana highlighted differing views. Ramesh criticised the scheme for alleged coercion and unauthorized enrollment, while Sitharaman defended its opt-out payment system. The scheme aims to benefit the economically disadvantaged with an 8% return.

title: Pakistan forces foil attack on naval base
description: Banned outfit Baluch Liberation Army (BLA) said fighters of its suicide unit, Majeed Brigade, mounted the raid and claimed they inflicted “heavy casualties” on the Pakistani forces. Last week, BLA terrorists had targeted a govt complex in Gwadar in the same province. “Forces in the vicinity were mobilised to support the naval troops. During the intense fire exchange, a 24-year-old sepoy was killed,” ISPR said in a statement.

title: UK social cohesion under threat from extremists: Report
description: UK report reveals ethnic harassment impact, intra-faith abuse, and rising tensions, recommending a new Office for Social Cohesion to address threats and extremist perpetrators.

title: India to triple N-power generation capacity by 2030: AEC chief
description: India plans to triple nuclear power capacity by 2030, emphasizing energy security and sustainable development. AEC chairman Mohanty highlights milestones in fast breeder reactor and international cooperation for nuclear energy expansion.

title: IPL: Chennai Super Kings thrash Gujarat Titans by 63 runs
description: Chennai Super Kings won their second match of the Indian Premier League 2024 with a 63-run victory over Gujarat Titans. The match played at MA Chidambaram Stadium saw CSK's batsmen displayed impressive cricketing talent, posting a total of 206 for 6. The Titans struggled to counter CSK's bowling attack, resulting in a disappointing loss.

title: Centre to consider revoking AFSPA in J&K: Amit Shah
Jaishankar backs Philippines in South China Sea, riles China
Watch: Dhoni's age-defying catch sends Chepauk into a frenzy
description: What's MS Dhoni's age? He's 42. But for the legendary wicketkeeper-batsman, it's just another number. Affectionately referred to as 'Thala' by his fans, Dhoni displayed his brilliance during the match against the Gujarat Titans. In his opening over, CSK's Daryl Mitchell sent down a full delivery around the off-stump to Vijay Shankar. Shankar aimed for a straight drive but ended up edging the ball instead.

title: Ex-army man from Kalimpong 'tricked' into Russian Army
Connectivity achieved by BRO for third axis to Ladakh
‘Not real money...': What Nikhil Kamath said Bengaluru's paper wealth
description: Nikhil Kamath, co-founder of Zerodha, has spoken about Bengaluru's wealth distribution focusing on paper assets in the tech industry, emphasizing the prevalence of stock options. “Paper money is complicated. Paper money gives you the appearance of wealth," he said.

title: Watch: Virat Kohli hugs an emotional Shikhar Dhawan
description: Virat Kohli and Shikhar Dhawan share a strong bond both on and off the cricket field. These two star batters have been teammates since their days playing for the Delhi state team, and their camaraderie continued as they represented India together for over a decade. Following Royal Challengers Bangalore's victory against Punjab Kings in the IPL 2024, Virat was observed consoling, embracing, and sharing a moment of laughter with his longtime teammate and friend, Dhawan.

title: Climate activist Sonam Wangchuk ends his 21-day hunger strike
Baltimore Bridge collapse: 'Ship issued mayday call before collision'
'Bat first, sorry bowl first': Gill's goof up at toss
description: The new skipper, Shubman Gill, seems to be gradually adapting to his role as captain. In just his second appearance for the toss as captain of the Gujarat Titans, Gill faced a perplexing moment after winning the coin toss against Chennai Super Kings on Tuesday.

title: How much salaries Google, OpenAI and Meta pay their AI scientists?
description: Top AI companies pay millions to AI scientists, with Meta struggling to match salaries, losing talent to rivals like OpenAI. Zuckerberg actively woos Deepmind researchers, offering lucrative deals to attract top talent.

title: King Charles, undergoing cancer treatment, to attend Easter service
description: King Charles, with Queen Camilla, will attend Easter service post-cancer diagnosis. The announcement from Buckingham Palace revealed that Charles, accompanied by Queen Camilla, will attend the Easter Sunday service at St. George's Chapel in Windsor on March 31. Prince William and Kate will be missing from the event. Charles, since his diagnosis, has reduced his public appearances as he undergoes treatment.

title: China seeks probe into suicide attack, Pak blames it on 'enemies'
'Yes, I am dark': Ex-India cricketer slams troll over racist attack
description: Former Indian cricket team spinner Laxman Sivaramakrishnan delivered a fitting response to a social media user attempting to troll him with a racist comment. Sivaramakrishnan, who represented India in 9 Tests and 16 ODIs from 1983 to 1987, shared a photo of himself with an elephant in the background, taken at the Ayyappan temple in Mahalingapuram, Tamil Nadu, on X (formerly Twitter).

title: US state bans Instagram, Tiktok, for kids under 14
description: DeSantis signs bill prohibiting under 14s from social media, requiring consent for 14-15s. Restricts under 16s from Facebook, Instagram, TikTok. Part of broader legislation with user age verification, following Arkansas, Ohio's lead.

title: Banks are closed for 14 days in April 2024; check full list
description: April 2024 brings 14 bank holidays for the new financial year, with celebrations like Ram Navami, Baisakhi. RBI's list impacts public, private banks, with operational internet banking services. Varying state-specific holidays and ATM services availability noted.

title: 'You have to finish it up': Trump to Israel on Gaza war
'Crew of container ship that collided with Baltimore bridge are all Indian'
Planes hit by mystery GPS jamming across Europe
description: Persistent GPS jamming in Eastern Europe affects 1,600 planes, impacting civilian flights near the Baltic Sea. Nato countries face disruptions, forcing pilots to resort to inertial navigation due to Russian jammers in Kaliningrad region.

title: The origin of 'Big Bang': Unraveling the true story
Congress MP Ravneet Singh Bittu joins BJP
'Kehte hai na ki jaisi sangati waisa...': Sehwag trolls PBKS
description: Virender Sehwag, renowned for his straightforward commentary style, showcased his trademark wit and humor while providing Hindi commentary during IPL 2024.

title: YouTube removed 2.25 million videos in India for these policy violations
PM speaks to BJP candidate who raised voice against TMC in Sandeshkhali
'India firmly supports Philippines': Jaishankar's swipe at China
UK court delays decision on Assange's last-ditch extradition appeal bid
description: The British High Court handed down a partial victory to WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange on Tuesday, saying he can't be immediately extradited to the United States on espionage charges and will be able to appeal against it. Two judges from the High Court have said that they will allow Julian Assange to pursue a new appeal unless US authorities provide additional assurances.

title: Bharti Singh reacts to not being a part of Kapil's upcoming show
description: Excitement mounts for The Great Indian Kapil Show on OTT, reuniting Kapil Sharma, Sunil Grover, and star-studded cast. Aamir Khan's addition promises global appeal, as fans eagerly anticipate the madness in the trailer. In an exclusive conversation with ETimes TV, Bharti Singh opened up about whether she would be a part of the show or not.

title: How Zuckerberg is 'working' on hiring talent from Google's AI teams
description: Tech companies, led by Meta's CEO Zuckerberg, intensify the AI arms race. Meta's unconventional recruiting methods emphasize AI development goals and scaling AI capabilities through large-scale GPU acquisitions.

title: 'We encourage fair legal process': US on arrest of Kejriwal
Watch: Virat Kohli's video call to family
description: Following his return from a two-month paternity break, the formidable batting force Virat Kohli delivered a match-winning performance, scoring 77 runs off 49 balls and securing a crucial four-wicket victory for Royal Challengers Bengaluru against Punjab Kings at the M. Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru. This triumph marked RCB's inaugural win in the tournament.

title: Looking to invest in NSCs? Know all the Tax benefits
description: NSC provides tax benefits and 7.7% interest rate for investors. Quarterly reviewed by the Ministry of Finance, NSC allows joint investments with a five-year lock-in period. Online account opening via DOP internet banking involves specific steps for interested individuals.

title: BJP's Dilip Ghosh makes controversial 'father' remark at Mamata
Delhi HC to hear Kejriwal's plea against arrest tomorrow
description: Arvind Kejriwal's arrest by ED over Delhi excise policy corruption involves kickbacks to AAP. He faces allegations of money laundering as chargesheets implicate him and his associates.

title: 'Mera hukum hai...' - Mrs & Mr Jadeja's banter delights fans
description: Ravindra Jadeja's wife, Rivaba, shared a photo in a 'Hukum' t-shirt at the CSK hotel, prompting a humorous response from her husband. CSK players are permitted to travel with families during an IPL season. The five-timer winners take on 2022 champions Gujarat Titans in a home game on Tuesday at the MA Chidambaram Stadium in Chennai.

title: Updated ITR filing deadline approaching
description: Taxpayers must address flagged transactions in AIS/Compliance Portal to meet the ITR deadline for FY 2020-21. Failure to respond accurately may lead to scrutiny or assessment by the tax department, potentially resulting in income tax notices.

title: RCB hit back: Kartik's 'trash' remark for Dayal gets cryptic response
description: Murali Kartik, India's former left-spinner, currently engaged in commentary duties for IPL 2024, found himself amidst controversy due to his comments regarding Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) pacer Yash Dayal.

title: Lok Sabha polls: BJP releases sixth list of candidates
Adani Green Energy Gallery opens in London's Science Museum
description: The Adani Green Energy Gallery at the Science Museum in London, led by Gautam Adani, highlights sustainability, transformative technology, and climate science. Through interactive exhibits and commissioned models, the gallery explores innovative energy solutions for a #SustainableFuture.

title: Sreejita De and Michael Blohm Pape have an intimate wedding reception
description: Sreejita De took a break from Shaitani Rasmein for her wedding reception in Kolkata with Michael Blohm-Pape. Despite fainting on set, she focused on immersive character preparation for her supernatural role.

title: Five Chinese killed in Pakistan explosion
description: Five Chinese nationals died in a northwest Pakistan convoy explosion by a suicide bomber. Balochistan Liberation Army attacked PNS Siddique airbase, causing one soldier's death. Pakistani forces killed five assailants and four terrorists in separate incidents.

title: India to start Test series against Australia in Perth
description: Cricket Australia named Perth as the venue for 1st Test in India-Australia series. The 5-Test series in November starts in Perth, ends in Sydney. Adelaide and Melbourne also host matches in December. Australia have not defeated India in a home Test series since 2014-15, losing both the 2018-19 and 2020-21 series. Australia defeated India in the World Test Championship final and in the 50-overs World Cup final last year.

title: Assembly polls: BJP releases list of candidates for by-polls
Watch: 'Senti kyu ho raha hai?' - Virat Kohli to...
description: Virat Kohli's comeback after an off-day against Chennai Super Kings guided Royal Challengers Bengaluru to victory over Punjab Kings in the IPL on Monday. The game saw a moment when Kohli had a cheeky banter while reacting to something he heard or saw, possibly a reaction to his dropped catch when he was on zero.

title: Ludhiana resident loses Rs 1.4 crore to online fraud: See details
Mistake believing ‘hype’ about growth: Raghuram Rajan
description: Rahuram Rajan cautioned against the dangers of complacency and the "hype" surrounding India's current success, advising that buying into such a narrative could hinder actual progress. He stressed that substantial and sustained efforts are required to convert potential into reality and warned against the false sense of achievement that politicians might promote.

title: Dell cut more jobs, here's what the filing reveals on layoffs
description: Dell cuts 6,000 jobs to streamline operations, focusing on CSG's net revenue growth despite challenges. A new return-to-office policy creates frustration among remote workers, impacting promotions and role changes.

title: Dream to be Musk or Ambani, why joint secretary: Sanjeev Sanyal
description: Economist Sanjeev Sanyal has said that people should not waste their time giving the UPSC exam. According to Sanjeev Sanyal, people should give the UPSC or the Union Public Service Commission exam only and only if they really want to be an administrator.

title: K Kavitha sent to judicial custody for 14 more days
description: The court has scheduled a hearing on April 1 for Kavitha's interim bail plea. Enforcement Directorate (ED) sought Kavitha's judicial custody through an application filed before the court. The ED stated that it is still exploring Kavitha's role in the case, identifying proceeds of crime, and uncovering others involved in related activities.

title: 'Titanic pose on scooty': Noida Police slap Rs 33,000 fine
description: During 2024 Holi celebrations, a woman's dangerous stunt mimicking the 'Titanic' pose led to a viral video. Noida Police issued fines for traffic violations, sparking online discussions on public safety and the risks of seeking viral fame.

title: 'Mandi known as Chota Kashi': Kangana's retort at Congress
description: Actress Kangana Ranaut, BJP's Lok Sabha candidate from Himachal's Mandi, expressed dismay over derogatory remarks about Mandi, known as "Chota Kashi". The comments by Congress leader Supriya Shrinate have stirred a political controversy before the upcoming elections. Earlier in her reaction to Supriya's objectionable remark, Kangana said that she has played various roles in movies and every woman deserves dignity.

title: Vehicles fall in water as Baltimore bridge collapses in US
International card spends to come under remittance scheme soon?
description: Indian banks are gearing up for changes in rules on international credit card spending under the liberalised remittance scheme (LRS). The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) plans to include overseas credit card transactions within the annual remittance cap. New regulations aim to regulate expenditures and tax collection on high-value expenses.

title: Judge throws out case filed by Musk's X against hate speech watchdog
description: California judge dismisses X's lawsuit against CCDH, ruling it was to punish speech. X accused CCDH of scare campaign. Legal action in July 2023. Surge in hate speech on X. Imran Ahmed affirms research rights.

title: Lok Sabha polls: BJP rules out alliance with SAD in Punjab
description: The BJP on Tuesday announced that it will contest the Lok Sabha elections alone in Punjab and ruled out an alliance with the Shiromani Akali Dal.Putting an end to speculation about a possible alliance with the SAD, BJP state unit chief Sunil Jakhar said "The BJP is going to contest the Lok Sabha elections alone in Punjab."

title: 'Solve health issues': CM Kejriwal issues 2nd order from jail
description: Kejriwal, despite being in ED custody, prioritized resolving health issues in Delhi. A planned protest at PM Modi's residence was denied by Delhi Police for security reasons. The INDIA bloc will hold a rally against Kejriwal's arrest.

title: Kailash Kher gifts himself the Jawa Perak Bobber worth Rs 2.13 lakh
description: Kailash Kher adds Jawa Perak bobber, reigniting passion for biking. Features 334cc engine, monoshock suspension, dual-channel ABS. Describes it as 'makkhan machine'. Jawa 350, 42, 42 Bobber also available.

title: Adani Group to acquire Gopalpur Port in Odisha for Rs 3,080 cr
description: Port major Adani Group has increased its presence on the east coast with Adani Ports entering into a definitive agreement to acquire Gopalpur Port Limited (GPL) at an enterprise value of Rs 3,080 crore. Gopalpur is a road-rail connected port with capacity of 20 MMTPA and significant potential for expansion.​

title: Mukhtar Ansari's health deteriorates in UP jail, taken to hosp
description: Gangster-turned-politician Mukhtar Ansari hospitalized in Banda Medical College ICU due to a urinary infection. Facing a life sentence, his son shared the news on social media. Transferred to ICU for surgery after being in district hospital. High security outside hospital. Convicted for arms license forgery, Ansari's health critical.

title: ‘Jai Hind, Bharat Mata Ki Jai' all coined by Muslims: Kerala CM
description: Pinarayi Vijayan condemns Sangh Parivar at an anti-CAA rally for bias against Muslims. He acknowledges Azimullah Khan for 'Bharat Mata Ki Jai' and Abid Hasan Safrani for 'Jai Hind'. Criticizes Congress's inaction during CAA protests.

title: Another 'century' for Virat Kohli in T20 cricket
description: The 35-year-old Virat Kohli showcased his vintage form after a disappointing outing against Chennai Super Kings in IPL 2024. The former RCB captain played a brilliant knock, scoring 77 runs off 49 balls, which earned him a distinguished record that only two batsmen have managed to achieve before him. RCB beat Punjab Kings by 4 wickets.

title: Badlapur murder: Neighbour kills 9-yr-old for Rs 20 L ransom
description: A nine-year-old boy was kidnapped and killed by a neighbour demanding ransom. Thane rural police arrested Safwan Maulavi, suspecting he needed money for a new house. The boy's body was buried at the construction site.

title: Sensex dips over 200 points, Nifty50 slips below 22,100
description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty, the Indian benchmark equity indices, started the week on a negative note on Tuesday. While BSE Sensex dipped over 200 points, Nifty50 slipped below 22,100. At 9:24 AM, BSE Sensex was trading at 72,693.62, down over 130 points or 0.19%. Nifty50 was at 22,069.50 down 27 points or 0.12%.

title: Alarm over cancer rates among under-50s post Kate's diagnosis
description: In response to Kate Middleton's unexpected cancer diagnosis, a global health concern has arisen regarding the increasing prevalence of cancer among individuals under 50. Scientists are urgently investigating potential causes, including environmental factors, lifestyle choices, and genetic predispositions. High-profile cases like Middleton's highlight the need for early detection and treatment.

title: MI's opening post-match ritual: Denial, optimism, rinse, repeat
description: To give it to Mumbai Indian, despite being poor starters, they have won the title five times. In fact in 2015, they won it despite losing four of their first five games. The year before, they qualified despite losing their first five games. They may do so again, but Sunday's loss had disturbing pointers.

title: I have still got it, I guess: Virat Kohli
description: Kohli, who took a two-month paternity break, scored a match-winning 77 off 49 balls with 11 fours and two sixes and also didn't forget to mention that whether it is cricket in the Olympic programme or T20 World Cup in the USA, he is 'The Face'. To RCB fans, he will always be, and continue to be, the 'King'.

title: Xiaomi CEO says he is putting his 'reputation on line' for this product
description: Lei Jun teases Xiaomi SU7 car under 500,000 yuan to rival Tesla, emphasizing smart design and tech. Xiaomi strategically enters EV market, backed by strong production capabilities and significant investment.

title: Read Microsoft memo on changes in its senior leadership
description: Microsoft appoints Pavan Davuluri as the new head of both Windows and Surface divisions, consolidating the teams under his leadership. The reorganization aims to take a more holistic approach to building silicon, systems, experiences, and devices.

title: 'Perplexed, disappointed': US after Israel cancels delegation visit
Can mutual fund investments be made in a child’s name?
description: An individual can invest in any mutual fund scheme on behalf of a child under 18 years old without any restrictions on the investment amount. The child will be the sole holder in the folio, with no joint holders allowed.

title: Putin says radical Islamists attacked Moscow, seeks Ukraine link
description: Russian authorities on Monday displayed footage of four men charged with executing an attack on a concert hall, after interrogations revealed they originated from Tajikistan. Within this group, two have admitted their involvement in the attack, according to announcements on the Moscow courts service's Telegram channel. These four individuals have been detained until May 22.

title: Elon Musk’s Starlink terminals are falling into wrong hands
description: Starlink, a SpaceX initiative, offers broadband internet via a network of approximately 5,500 satellites launched since 2019. Currently serving about 2.6 million customers, Starlink is poised to significantly boost SpaceX's revenue. Initially founded by Elon Musk with the vision of Mars exploration, SpaceX has evolved into a key player in the US government’s space program and a major contributor to national security.

title: Gujarat Titans' TN factor can make it tough for CSK
description: The beauty of franchise cricket is such that the visiting Titans side will consist of five 'locals', while Super Kings, the only IPL team from the state, have none from the region. The Titans playing pack comprises five TN members, who know the Chepauk pitches like the back of their palms.

title: Ericsson to cut 1,200 jobs: All the details
description: Ericsson plans 1,200 job cuts in Sweden as part of global initiatives to streamline operations and navigate economic uncertainty in the challenging 2024 mobile networks market.

title: Pakistan's second largest airbase attacked
description: Pakistan's second largest airbase, PNS Siddique on Tuesday came under attack by multiple explosions and gunfire, according to several media reports.The Balochistan Liberation Army (BLA) has claimed responsibility for the assault on the Naval Airbase in Turbat, citing opposition to Chinese investments in Balochistan's resources. The BLA claims that its members have breached the airbase, where Chinese drones are reportedly stationed.

title: Telecom giant lays off hundreds of employees in video meetings
description: Bell laid off 400+ workers, condemned by Unifor for impersonal terminations. Bell defended the process, citing transparency. The union continues to protest prioritizing shareholder payouts over employees in necessary restructuring.

title: Two patients' blood bags swapped at Pune's Aundh hospital
description: Two patients at Aundh Civil Hospital received wrong blood types, leading to ICU admission. Nurse mix-up caused haemolysis, organ shutdown. Ongoing investigation and strict actions by hospital administration. Relatives allege nurse's phone distraction during transfusion.

title: Forest fires singe Telangana wildlife sanctuaries
description: Telangana combating forest fires in Tadvai region of Eturnagaram Sanctuary and Amrabad Reserve. RM Dobriyal highlights challenges and the need for disaster management inclusion for better assistance.

title: Trump’s net worth hits $6.5 billion
description: A state appeals court significantly reduced the bond Trump had to post in a New York fraud lawsuit from over $500 million to $175 million.. Concurrently, Trump Media & Technology Group concluded a merger lasting 29 months, leading to Trump owning shares now valued in the billions. Consequently, Trump's net worth surged by over $4 billion, propelling him into Bloomberg Billionaires Index's top 500 for the first time.

title: China hacked poll panel, behind cyber attacks on MPs: UK
description: The UK govt revealed on Monday that China was behind a wave of cyber attacks against MPs and peers, as well as a hack on the electoral commission accessing personal details of over 40 million voters. The UK govt said the National Cyber Security Centre assessed it's highly likely China state-affiliated cyber actor APT31 conducted reconnaissance activity against parliamentarians in 2021. The govt has sanctioned a front company and two actors involved in the operations of APT31.
